      "content": "It makes sense that you're frustrated when people feel like they're trying to repair a ghost; no amount of advice can bring back a version of you that feels dead to you. Since the person you were seems truly gone, perhaps the only way forward is to stop fighting a battle against a dead weight and instead focus on surviving and finding meaning in the space you occupy now. If that role of the \"shell\" feels like the only reality left, you might consider slowing down to see where the next small, unexpected step could take you, rather than forcing yourself to chase a dream that no longer exists.",
